Cooper Ave., north side, between 60th Place (left) and 61st Street (right), showing the John Moses De Bevoise house. This house and land was purchased by the above owner from one Remsen. The small wing stood during the Revolutionary War. The large wing was erected after the war. It was moved, location unknown, by Richard Weber in 1910.
About 1909.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
